    "millsfield:images_texts": [
      "OLYMPIC\nWinter Schedules\nU.S./ CANADA/EUROPE/MIDDLE EAST/AFRICA\nNOVEMBER 1, 1970 — MARCH 31, 1971",
      "London a\nAmsterdam\n• Hamburg\nBrussels\nGeneva®\nParis\nZurich\nMunich\nFrankfurt\n• Vienna\nMontreal\nRome\n• Salonica\nChicago\nNew York •\nATHENS\n@Istanbul\n• Rhodes\n• Nicosia\nBeirut\n•Tel Aviv\n• Cairo\nYOU\nHAVE AN\nOLYMPIC TEAM\nGOING FOR\nYOU.\nOLYMPIC AIRWAYS has established an enviable reputation for elegant service, spon-\ntaneous and warm-hearted hospitality and absolute dependability. Thousands of pas-\nsengers yearly fly the OLYMPIC way, on business or on holiday, through Athens,\nthe Golden Gate of Greece. Athens is also the gateway to the beauties of ancient and\nmodern Greece, its incomparable antiquities and beautiful beaches, its ever-chang-\ning landscape and its countless picturesque islands. Frequent domestic schedules\nbring the remotest destinations within easy reach, and from there, your exploration of\nGreece can begin.\nNairobi\nJohannesburg"
    ],
